Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
dumpCongestArea(25.10)                                  dumpCongestArea(25.10)

Name
       dumpCongestArea - Writes the routing congestion information to an ASCll
       output file

Syntax
       dumpCongestArea

       [-help]

       <file_name>

       [-all]

       Writes  the routing congestion information to an ASCll output file. The
       output file reports the coordinates of overflow cells, vertical tracks,
       and horizontal tracks. You can use the  dumpCongestArea  command  after
       running  Early Global Route.

Parameters
       -all   Writes  the  congestion information for all gcells in the design
              to the specified  output  file,  regardless  of  the  congestion
              level.  If  the  -all  parameter  is not specified, this command
              writes the congestion information for only  the  most  congested
              gcells in the design to the specified output file.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       <file_name>
              Specifies  the  name  of the output file to which the congestion
              information is written.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each dumpCongestArea parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man dumpCongestArea.

Example
              * The  following  command writes the routing congestion informa-
                tion for all gcells to the congest.txt file:

                dumpCongestArea -all congest.txt

Related Information
              * dumpNanoCongestArea

              * dumpNetsInCongestedArea

              * reportCongestArea

              * Using Early Global Route for Congestion  and  Timing  Analysis
                chapter in the Innovus User Guide

